##Comparing strings

C developers have the strcmp() function for comparing strings. In JavaScript, you just use the less-than and greater-than operators:

	var a = "a";
	var b = "b";
	if (a < b) // true
	  print(a + " is less than " + b);
	else if (a > b)
	  print(a + " is greater than " + b);
	else
